text.tspan: Lead concentrations in the blood of children in the United States
Lead concentrations measured in blood samples from children aged one to five years old. Children are particularly
vulnerable to lead poisoning and can suffer permanent impacts on the development of the brain and nervous system.

text.textPath: 5 µg/dL = WHO maximum threshold for lead exposure
5 µg/dL = WHO maximum threshold for lead exposure

text.tspan: Source: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention; National Center for Health Statistics
